Tags.string 'NodeComment':
A lamp can have several triggers and are used as feedback for the player. For example for a door, when more than one trigger is needed to indicate that a needed trigger like a pressure plate is active.
If no tigger is set, the lamp is always switched on.
If the level designer did not add any triggers to the array, the lamp will be switched on by default. If there are triggers it is switched off instead.
This setup is the same as the door. Check there for more details.  If you use identical behavior across different actors, consider moving it to its own component.
The Dynamic Material reference for the lamp was saved in the construction script. The emmissive parameter is changed when it is switched on or off.
Create dynamic material to change the color and emmisive values on activation.
